text: But the jet aircraft was already miles away, swinging down to the darkening earth. "It passed me at fifty thousand feet, sir. It was climbing steadily." Group Captain Llewelyn Jones, Officer Commanding R.A.F. Station, Dinas, looked keenly at the Flying Officer who had burst so unceremoniously into his office. "And what did it look like, Broughtons? Some sort of rocket?"
